T1  - The Box Spread Arbitrage Conditions: Theory, Tests, and Investment Strategies
PY  - 1989
Y1  - 1989/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/2.1.91
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 2
IS  - 1
SP  - 91
EP  - 108
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This paper develops and tests arbitrage bounds for a combination of two option spread positions known as a box spread. This strategy involves the simultaneous use of four options and creates a position that is equivalent to riskless lending. The no-arbitrage conditions are compared to existing arbitrage bounds and are tested using Chicago Board Options Exchange data.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/2.1.91
ER  - 



